Hey everyone that reads this. Nothing much happened this weekend, nothing exciting at all really. I have been thinking about something a lot lately, and I think I'll share it with you. I've just been wondering, what is the point of life? Why are we here? I mean, I don't understand what humans are meant to do, what is our purpose? Fight and kill each other in pointless wars? Find love, and live happily ever after? I just don't understand what the fuck we do everything for? I guess these are questions that can never be answered or understood. I just don't understand what the point of anything we do is, I just don't get anything. And, maybe its just to try and be as happy as you can be. But really, look around, look at the world we are living in people. There is really much to be happy about, its a fucked up world, with fucked up people. People are murder, raped, beaten, abused, used, taken advantage of every hour of the day. I don't think a lot of people think about that, because it doesn't concern them..but if you take another look, you will see the fucked up world this is, and how fucked up everything is. So, if people are killed, what the fuck was their point? Nothing I guess. But why? I think people take their lives for granted, sure it has no point to what anybody can tell, but just please for this moment, think about how fucking lucky you are. That you aren't cut up in a fucking ditch, or you aren't being raped, or that you aren't living on the streets fucked up on drugs, and having no life at all. Don't take your life for granted, because its short, and fucked up. So live as much as you can. I'm done fucking rambling, later.

Anyways, on with the show. It was fucking amazing, although I didn't get to stay long enough to get to see Bleeding Through because I had to leave at 10. But the rest of the bands we fucking awesome. It was the best show I have been to in a long while. Jake might have broken his hand, and he suffered "severe tissue damage" as the doctor put it.
